\subsection{Translation}
Define $\Gamma^*$ which takes a context and yields a context.
\[ (\Gamma, x : A)^* = (\Gamma^*, x : A^*)\]
\[ \sem {\Gamma, x : A} = (\sem \Gamma, x : A^*, x' : \sem A (x))\]
Define $A^*$ which takes a type and yields a type.
\[ ((a: A) \to B)^* = (a : A^*) \to B^* \]
Define $\sem A(M)$ which takes a type $A$ and a term of type $A^*$
and yields a type.
\[ \sem{(a : A) \to B}(f) = (a : A^*) (a' : \sem A(a))\to  \sem B (f\ a) \]

Define $M^*$ which takes a term and yields a term.
\[ x^* = x \]
\[ \sem x = x' \]
\[ (\lambda x . M)^* = \lambda x . M^* \]
\[\sem {\lambda x . M} = \lambda x.\lambda x'. \sem M\]
\[(M\ N)^* = M^*\ N^*\]
