\[= (\Gamma^*, x:A^*)\]
\[= (\Gamma, x:A)^*\]
For case $(\Gamma, x::A\simp)$ we can reason
\[\sem{((\Gamma, x::A\simp)^*)\locking} = \sem{(\Gamma^*, x:A\simp)\locking}\]
\[= \sem{((\Gamma^*)\locking, x::A\simp)}\]
\[= (\sem{(\Gamma^*)\locking}, x:A\simp)\]
\[= (\Gamma^*, x:A\simp)\]
\[= (\Gamma, x::A\simp)^*\]
\cqed
\end{proof}

